{"title":"Ride Metal: John Takes Miguel on the Town to Towers Santa Fe Gravel Ride – Miguel Ovalles & John Watson","link":"https://theradavist.com/santa-fe-gravel-town-to-towers-ride/","date":1719484767000,"content":"<p><em>In our latest Race Metal video series, <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/maocycle\" target=\"_blank\">Miguel</a> asked John what his favorite gravel route is in <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/search/santa+fe/\" target=\"_blank\">Santa Fe</a>, prompting John to take Miguel along for an all-day epic. The ride starts in the Railyard District in Santa Fe and tops out at the radio towers on Tesuque Peak. Check out the video above and a short gallery below from the full Town to Towers Gravel Ride!</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-9.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-9.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-9.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-9.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-9.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-14.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-14.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-14.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-14.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-14.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<h3>Things to Know</h3>\n<p>In the summer, it’s best to get started early, as the pavement to the start of the dirt on Pacheco Canyon Road gets hot. Bring a water filter to refill along the streams and tire repair kits like a <a href=\"https://shop.theradavist.com/products/dynaplug%C2%AE-racer-pro-obsidian-radavist-edition\" target=\"_blank\">Dynaplug</a>. You can meet in town at Sky Coffee and grab a burrito. We’d recommend a minimum of a 40 mm tire. The descent off the top is a bone-rattler. The ride takes about 6 hours to complete.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2885\" height=\"1924\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/MiguelBike.jpg?fit=1200,1924&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/MiguelBike.jpg?w=2885&amp;quality=75 2885w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/MiguelBike.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/MiguelBike.jpg?resize=2000,1334&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/MiguelBike.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/MiguelBike.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/MiguelBike.jpg?resize=2048,1366&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2885\" height=\"1924\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/JohnBike.jpg?fit=1200,1924&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/JohnBike.jpg?w=2885&amp;quality=75 2885w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/JohnBike.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/JohnBike.jpg?resize=2000,1334&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/JohnBike.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/JohnBike.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/JohnBike.jpg?resize=2048,1366&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<h3>The Bikes</h3>\n<p>Miguel was riding his <a href=\"https://beachclubbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Beach Club Al Dente</a> with 700 x 43 mm wheels, and John was on his <a href=\"https://meriwethercycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Meriwether Cycles</a> OGATB adventure bike with 2.3″ 29er wheels.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>The Route</h3>\n<p></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-13.jpg?fit=1200,1600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-13.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-13.jpg?resize=1200,960&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-13.jpg?resize=768,614&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-13.jpg?resize=1536,1229&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-20.jpg?fit=1200,1600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-20.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-20.jpg?resize=1200,960&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-20.jpg?resize=768,614&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-20.jpg?resize=1536,1229&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-24.jpg?fit=1200,1600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-24.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/TownTowersGravelMiguel-